<br>
Increase Armor Class (AC) by 17 (L55)<br>
Increase Strength by 60 (L55)<br>
Increase Attack Speed by 65% (L55)<br>
<br>
This spell line clearly would be almost too valuable when compared to many other buffs from other classes if castable on PCs.   It is plainly one of the best buffs in the game -- rightfully so for PETs, as the Mage pet is often ignored / overlooked by the classes that cast buffs.<br>
<br>
Besides, getting back to my original point with these wish list type of threads:   What do you want, Mages?   Do you want to be a buffer?  Or some ad-hoc junkyard type of class? Or a big generalist like Druids?  Or a damage-doer?<br>
<br>
I'll take a tough pet and awesome nukes over being able to cast burnout on tanks, thank you very much.<br>
<br>
As a Mage, I want to be at the point of battle, dealing out effective, massive, damage, damage, damage, and more damage with my nukes and my pets along side the Rogue and the Wizard.<br>
<br>
We have enough utility, thanks.   I like our DS line and some of our Summons.  I like the foci.  I like the debuffs.   I look forward very much to CoH and mod rod II.   But, frankly, thats enough of that kind of stuff and get back to our roots, IMOHO. <p><u>Seek Pyremaker</u><br>
Mage 54th Season, Xegony<br>
The Ring of Truth
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 559<br> <font color=#333333>(4/16/02 10:15:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: k</span><hr size=1> This is the reason why magicians will never get anything done and we will stay forever gimped.<br>
<br>
When a fellow magician makes a statement about things they would like to see the &quot;Everything is right in mage world&quot; people like &quot;Rhasin&quot; love to come out and attack them. Calling his ideas laughable was a insult IMHO but I am sure he will not see it that way.<br>
<br>
On to the point. I have two views on magician issues as they stand. Reading this board over the past week has really made me care less about what improvements magicians get. The bitterness of alot of magicians is at a all time high and there seems to be a nasty war between the mage that wants to return to the pre-kunark blaster and the mage that is happy to be a mod rod whore.<br>
<br>
Personally I would like to see two things happen depending on which direction VI pushes the class.  If magicians are not going to be given there damage dealer ability back then I feel we need great improvements in utility. I have come to terms with the fact I might never be again what I was pre-kunark. If that is so give me major utility. A few utility things I can list off the top of my head is...<br>
<br>
A group Phantom Armor spell<br>
<br>
A better regen spell that stacks with Phantom Armor, I am going to go as far as saying give us chloroplast. That would fix alot of the mana regen issues. With 10hp regen on top of phantom armor and Zland heart I can match C2 mana regen already. The balance is that I have to give up health unlike clarity.<br>
<br>
Some focus items with int. Resist are not to big of a deal really. If you are in a uber guild then most of the great items you are wearing have resist on them and with bard songs and druid spells resist are at 255 easy anyway.  For the magician that isnt &quot;Uber&quot; giving up 5 slots with no int is to great of a pain.<br>
<br>
Give magicians a upgrade to summon companion that works like CoTH. That way if our pet wanders off we can summon it back and clear the hate list. If we can do it for players why on earth would it be overpowered for a floating blob.<br>
<br>
They gave necromancers group buffs for groups well magicians should have the same.  Some str and atk group buffs that could be cast on others would make magicians more wanted in groups. Nice atk buffs alone would be of great benefit.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now if the goal is to return magicians to there dominate damage dealer role then a few things can be done....<br>
<br>
Increase our DD power. If &quot;bolts&quot; are out strong point then give us a line of power bolt spells that are in line with the scaling of power pre-kunark. A 1400dd bolt isnt overpowered when you look at the fact of how hard it is to land bolts on raids. Also bolts can miss and they do and that is where the balance lies. Also a upgrade to scares would be nice.<br>
<br>
Across the board increases in pet power starting at lvl 51. Un-nerf the monster summoning line of spells.  Move Shock of Steel down to lvl 54 or 55 and give us a new magic based nuke at lvl 58-60 that does around 1250dd. <br>
<br>
Better summoned armor (with resist and atk) for pets. Also expand on the Sword of Runes line. If beastlords can give there pet unresistable procs at lvl 52 then magicians should be able to summon procing weapons for our pets that are not resistable.  Improve the lvl 60 heal for pets. 400m for 900hps isnt very good. 400m for 1500hps maybe but 900 is way to low. <br>
<br>
Fire pets are gimp...give them wizard stun spells and no damage shield. Also give them a better rune line of spells to cast on themselves. I am for removing all melee damage from this pet so that the nuke damage can be increased.<br>
<br>
Escape pets please!<br>
<br>
DDD this pet rocks...do not make this a escape pet. Increase the lvl so this pet is on par with GV pets. Increase the melee damage output on this pet also. OMG I love this pet and it is the only one I use while solo. Me and my enchanter bud do efreeti every night and the enchanter is able to slow and tash and the pet can still hold taunt. Also a lvl 50 version of this pet would be nice.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anti-summoning spell would be nice as well. <br>
<br>
<br>
