All told, a Magician's pet + spells should be equal or greater than a Wizard's total damage output, in my opinion, on the order of how a rogue's damage output exceeds a warriors. Our spells should not be greater than a wizards, and when gimped by lure only mobs and relying on pet damage only, should be perhaps on par with them. <br>
<br>
It's really questionable to me whether any improvements to the Magician class should be done through an improvement in the pets (higher hitting, etc), or in spells. Each avenue holds advantages, but as many people have noted, Magicians are half pet, half spellcaster. As our pet's power increases, our spell damage decreases to keep a balance and prevent us from being overpowered. As our spell power increases, our pets may be overlooked or reviewed and dismissed from any improvements. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
