<br>
I've been away from EQ for over a year.  It's been about 16 months since I last played a post-50 character.  So take what I have to say with a grain of salt.<br>
<br>
Since their inception, mages have whined about something regarding their class.  We whined about necro's equipping their pets with weapons and we couldn't, we whined about nobody wanting our summoned items, we whined about lack of mana regen, we whined about chain research, we whined about only the earth pet being any good at 49, etc., etc., ad nauseum.<br>
<br>
Not saying we were any better or worse than the whiners in other classes.  But we did whine.<br>
<br>
Pre-Kunark, we were good damage dealers.  You can argue whether or not we were better than necro's or druids overall, but we made wizzies look sick when you added in our pet damage.<br>
<br>
Post-Kunark, other classes were improved in damage dealing whereas we stayed mostly the same.  Our summons were improved, we could equip weapons on our pets but it no longer made a difference, and we have some forms of mana and hp regens.<br>
<br>
Our pets stayed roughly the same, other than for the epic pet and the fire pet, and our dd spells were improved somewhat.  It didn't matter though, because of the ungodly resists at the high end of the game.<br>
<br>
Melee output went up significantly.  Healing abilities went up significantly.  High resists meant that tactics shifted away from casters killing high-end mobs to melee killing them.  And wizzies were no longer a joke with their lure spells and improved DD's.<br>
<br>
We were no longer primary damage dealers.  Instead, we shifted to a support role.  Mod rods, summoned items, malo's, nukes when we had a chance.  No pets, since pathing and aoe fear spells made them useless.<br>
<br>
Post Kunark mages seem to be more accepting of this role.  Those of us who remember our roles prior to Kunark seem to be less accepting.<br>
<br>
Ok, that's my summary... what can we do?<br>
<br>
1. Re-examine pet strength overall.  After Kunark, VI said that pets were as strong as they were ever going to be.  Is that still true?  Even with the ungodly hp's of Velious mobs?  Is it true for Luclin and PoP?<br>
<br>
2. Fix the damn fire pet.  Everyone hates it.  Make it mo' better.<br>
<br>
3. Provide mages with a way to buff the resists and damage output of their pets past what we have.  You can do this with either direct cast spells, or summoned items al la the Muzzle of Mardu.  Personally, I would make you choose between improving resists and increasing damage output, like the old sword of runes that proc'ed on everything vs. a dagger of symbols.  But give pets a chance of resisting stuff.<br>
<br>
4. Provide mages with a way of improving their chances of DD spells not being resisted.  Maybe do this via AAXP - an ability that allows you to lower the damage done by a spell to radically increase its chance of landing.  Tinker with the percentages to keep wizzies happy, but restore our role as 2nd best damage dealer.<br>
<br>
5. Provide mages with a way to combat AoE fear and bad pathing.  Maybe an AAXP ability like /pet hold that wipes fear.  Or the idea of making pets neutral unless told to attack something, combined with summon companion.<br>
<br>
6. Give mages a way to regen mana earlier and better than what we have today.  A lesser mod rod available at level 20, maybe, that would work either on us OR ON OUR PETS.  Let me sponge off the pet's hp's to either reduce downtime or cannibilize it for one last spell.  Or, give me a version of Reclaim Energy that's not all or nothing.<br>
<br>
7. FOR GOD's SAKE, give us a better chance to summon a max level pet... either via increased malachite usage or a focus item or ??? (sorry, pet peeve :-)<br>
<br>
I'm sure I've missed something, but as I told you, take everything I have to say with a grain of salt given my lack of recent experience.<br>
<br>
And if there's misspellings or bad grammar, well I'm not using preview to check.  You're stuck with them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 625<br> <font color=#333333>(4/25/02 1:53:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: k</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1. Re-examine pet strength overall. After Kunark, VI said that pets were as strong as they were ever going to be. Is that still true? Even with the ungodly hp's of Velious mobs? Is it true for Luclin and PoP?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
